U.K. Stocks Resume Retreat; ARM, Inmarsat Decline as Lloyds Shares Advance

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-21T08:04:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/u-k-stocks-resume-retreat-arm-inmarsat-decline-as-lloyds-shares-advance.html
U.K. stocks resumed their retreat
after briefly erasing losses.  The FTSE 100 Index slid 0.2 percent to 5,353.22 at 8:59
a.m. in  London . The gauge fell as much as 0.8 percent at the
open of trading.  Inmarsat Plc and Arm Holdings Plc paced declining shares,
falling 2.1 percent and 1.9 percent respectively. Lloyds Banking
Group Plc gained 3.1 percent, the best performer on the FTSE
100.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  